    <h3>District Information</h3>
    <p>This district is distinctly known and honored for its work with Advanced Placement (AP) courses. Green Bay is one of 367 school districts in the nation being honored by the College Board, the governing body of AP classes and the SATS, on its AP achievement list for opening courses to a significantly broader pool of students, while maintaining or improving the percentage of students earning scores of 3 out of 5 (the minimum for college credit) or higher. The district's mission of "Embracing learning for all as our highest priority," rings true more now than ever. Offering 17 different AP courses while still maintaining one of the highest levels of public education in the nation is what keeps families, generation after generation, in Green Bay. Having one of the most progressive initiatives of developing a contract between teachers and students, while focusing on learning outcomes, with optimal working conditions, is just one of the many things making these schools the most modeled in the country.
</p>
